        public abstract Pointer wrap​(T object)
        Wraps the specified instance of the base interface/class with a native implementation and returns the allocated Pointer. It is likely that the returned Pointer will be a unique pointer.
        Parameters:
        object - The object
        Returns:
        A Pointer to a native implementation of the corresponding base interface/class whose calls are serviced via the specified Java object.

      • wrap

        public Pointer wrap​(T object,
                    boolean doIntern)
        Wraps the specified instance of the base interface/class with a native implementation and returns the allocated Pointer. It is likely that the returned Pointer will be a unique pointer.
        Parameters:
        object - The object
        doIntern - If true, interns the pointer for subsequent lookups via #find(T)
        Returns:
        A Pointer to a native implementation of the corresponding base interface/class whose calls are serviced via the specified Java object.

      • destruct

        public abstract void destruct​(Pointer pointer)
        Destructs the pointer memory for a Pointer instance returned by clone(long) or wrap(Object).

        Results will be undefined (application will likely crash) if this method is invoked on a Pointer that was returned from any methods other than clone(long) or wrap(Object) on the Interop instance for a given base interface/class.

        Parameters:
        pointer - The pointer

        public long castToPointer​(java.lang.Class<?> as,
                          T obj)
        Performs a native cast of the pointer wrapped by obj.
        Parameters:
        as - The managed type for the corresponding native pointer
        obj - A managed object wrapping a native pointer
        Returns:
        A pointer to the native type corresponding to the managed class as or 0L if the source object either 1) does not have a pointer or 2) the native type cannot be cast as desired.
